                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-07-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is absolutely awesome! Zimmerman has a nice, easy to read style of writing. His explanations are clear and concise, with great diagrams. Best of all, he doesn't take himself to seriously. He goes to great lengths to make it all seem so easy. I'd recommend this book to anyone that wants to understand how every aspect of a motorcycle works,want's to perform their own manitenance, or at very least wants to understand why the dealer is charging them so much for the repairs. In my opinion this one is top shelf.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Basics to advanced are covered</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
